Once upon a time, I had version metadata properly imbued into the Windows plugin DLLs using the file `dfx-library/dfxplugin-version.rc`.  It could pre-process the `*-def.h` prefix header files (and relied on some macros defined in those to populate the version info), and so it would involve adding something like this into the `win32/resource.rc` files:

```
#include "geometer-def.h"
#include "../../dfx-library/visualstudio/dfxplugin-version.rc"
```

Perhaps if interested, you could see whether it might be easy enough to reintegrate this?

```
   // Super simple layout since I think the museum might be doomed;
   // we can make it a nice table again if we keep it
```

I'm adding a couple of issues for @tom7 that I found notes about while reorganizing the "extras" page, and which both were actually things that I had also been meaning to ask you about.

This one is the full-size image zoom that happens when you click on a plugin's thumbnail image.  I saw your comments:
```
    function FullImage(f) {
      // XXX improve!
      window.location = f;
    }
```
I'm not sure what exactly you were thinking in terms of improvements, but I was thinking it would be nicer if the full-size image appeared as an overlay in the current browser window/tab rather than in a new window (as I implemented it so many years ago with my novice javascript chops).  Opening a new window for an image feels kinda hostile to the 21st century web browsing experience.  Plus crops the bottom and looks bad in Safari (and perhaps other browsers, but not Chrome).
